    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="268"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">McKenzie</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 115.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. Hicks’s No. 425, of September
                    16, 1892, and previous correspondence in regard to the claim of the Hydrographic
                    Commission of the Amazon against Peru, the justice of which has been
                    acknowledged by the Peruvian Government, I inclose a copy of a letter<note n="*"
                        xml:id="d268fn1">Not printed.</note> from Mr. William Shands, executor of
                    one of the claimants, urging that the claim may be pressed to a conclusion.</p>
                <p>You will ascertain whether there is any prospect of obtaining its payment.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
